WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:01.520 --> 00:00:06.260
From the Library of
Congress in Washington DC.

00:00:17.350 --> 00:00:19.200
Hi. I'm John Brown.

00:00:19.200 --> 00:00:22.010
In this edition of the
BARD Mobile How-To Series,

00:00:22.010 --> 00:00:25.200
we are going to cover
adjusting the font and contrast.

00:00:25.200 --> 00:00:30.380
From the settings tab in BARD
Mobile, select Visual settings.

00:00:30.380 --> 00:00:34.130
To adjust the font
size, tap Font size.

00:00:34.130 --> 00:00:37.410
BARD Mobile will present you with
the following options: small,

00:00:37.410 --> 00:00:41.120
medium, large, and extra large.

00:00:41.120 --> 00:00:46.540
On the iPhone and iPod touch, small
is 12 point type; medium is 18,

00:00:46.540 --> 00:00:50.520
large is 24, and extra large is 30.

00:00:50.520 --> 00:00:54.700
On the iPad, small
is 16; medium is 24;

00:00:54.700 --> 00:00:58.580
large is 32; and extra large is 40.

00:00:58.580 --> 00:01:00.550
Tap the desired size.

00:01:00.550 --> 00:01:03.140
Note that the default
is set to medium.

00:01:03.140 --> 00:01:08.480
To adjust the contrast, go to
the settings tab in BARD Mobile.

00:01:08.480 --> 00:01:12.920
From there, select Visual
settings, then contrast.

00:01:12.920 --> 00:01:15.840
BARD Mobile will present you
with the following options:

00:01:15.840 --> 00:01:20.740
black text on a white background,
white text on a black background,

00:01:20.740 --> 00:01:22.920
black text on a yellow background,

00:01:22.920 --> 00:01:26.010
or yellow text on a
black background.

00:01:26.010 --> 00:01:28.160
Tap the desired contrast.

00:01:28.160 --> 00:01:31.930
Note that the default is set to
black text on a white background.

00:01:31.930 --> 00:01:37.610
This has been a presentation
of the Library of Congress.

00:01:37.610 --> 00:01:40.520
Visit us at loc.gov.

